      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp",
      "name": "Choke Slam",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per round</p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong> Cabbagehead has a creature @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Grabbed]{Grabbed} or @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Restrained]{Restrained}</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> Cabbagehead slams the creature against a nearby surface. The target and the surface struck each take [[/r {3d6}[bludgeoning]]]{3d6 bludgeoning damage}, and the target must succeed at a @Check[type:fortitude|dc:20] save or become @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Slowed]{Slowed 1} for 1 round, or stunned for 1 round on a critical failure.</p>"
